caption: My favorite sushi location in Brooklyn by far. Amazing chirashi bowl and omakase
Tasty ramen! Good outdoor seating!
Not great experience 😕
Not bad. Nothing to write home about. Good service.
Love this place. High quality fish, great service, and totally underrated!
Great food and great service!
Very good sushi, will order again.

I feel like rewarding myself, I get omakase. I ordered the sushi omakase at the bar and was pleasantly surprised at the array I was given. I eat everything, so I gave the chef the okay to hand me whatever pieces he desired. Appetizers, sushi, one hand roll, and dessert is included. There was a good mix of blue fish and classic pieces like toro. Unlike many sushi restaurants that offer omakase I've been to, this place gives you a bigger cut of fish. My only complaint is that sometimes I got very large, concentrated amounts of wasabi. I love wasabi, but the amount was inconsistent and overpowering at times, covering up the taste of the fish.

It's our favourite restaurant in the area. Me and my husband Oliver go there a LOT. The Sushi is amazing and the atmosphere is welcoming and friendly. It's a lovely place.

Very clean and convenient restaurant. They serve large portions and for affordable prices. We enjoyed the meals a lot and the waiters were very personal and explanatory. Highly recommended.
Chicken taste fake waste of my money
Fresh ingredients. Chef Leo would only serve you the best.
Great food, good service
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I got to say their customer service is always good and they keep the spot clean at all times. Rates are affordable and they serve generous portions.
The soft shell crab is fantastic!
They have very good food special the sushi dishes.

Came here during COVID and gotta say that I was thoroughly impressed! The sushi was fresh even with the lower volume of people. And nothing beats the value in Park  Slope!  Update: Came here again. Was great again!
Tried sushi here for the the first time and it was so delicious. I'm planing on coming back next week for more.

Loved the 10 piece omakase, every piece is treated with respect and brushed with it's own sauce pairing. The special rolls are also prepared with fresh fish and has a light flavorful touch. It's not drowned in sauces or dressings so as to cover low quality tasteless fish. I can taste every piece is made with love and this is soul food. Thank you Chef!

This place is SO good and underrated. I got a kaisen don (rice bowl with sashimi, uni and ikura) which was delicious, and the restaurant used high-quality fish. I love that their seaweed salad is REAL seaweed not the neon green stuff.

My new found go-to sushi joint after Geido closed for the pandemic. The amaebi tempura is one of the most crunchy delicious tempura I had for awhile, sashimi deluxe is fresh with various fishes to chomp into and I love the yellow tail roll but it will be much better if it has some scallions in it.

Tonight I ordered a Happy Summer Roll, Dancing Eel roll and a Volcano roll. ALL were very good. Everything was fresh including the wasabi I asked for. Staff was friendly and helpful. Place was clean and everyone wore masks still. I’ll definitely return!
Yummy Sushi!
Not the largest or cheapest menu,  but the sushi,  maki,  and sashimi quality is great.

Very enjoyable lunch here, good service and good sushi. The sashimi deluxe had more a variety of fish than I often see. Normally when I ask for a side of avocado I can expect 3 slices, but here I'm pretty sure they gave me half an entire avocado's worth of slices.
The meals and service were ahead of my expectations. I truly loved the atmosphere of this spot. Nice place to take the family out for dinner.
Best kept secret in Brooklyn!
Small but cute and delicious sushi bar! The fish is fresh and the apps are delicious.

A nice place with a small twist on tipical sushi served in NYC. I love seaweed salad and Yashin's was the most interesting. It has several varieties on the plate. Also you can have omakase or order individual items from the omakase section.
Here is a pic of my salmon. You be the judge. No way I'm Eating that

It's a fantastic place for sushi!

Good fresh fish

Sushi was excellent, fresh & well prepared. Staff is very friendly, English may sometimes be a problem but a little patience can be extremely rewarding as the food is very very good. Also the staff is anxious to be helpful. The Omakase is one of the best bargains in the city. The chicken teriyaki is a favorite and the spinach salad is different and a must along with a variety of other dishes. Two thumbs up 👍 with a definite recommendation. Well worth visiting 😊
Phenomenal sushi.

Came here with my family which filled up half the space during dinner. It's a small restaurant, max 16? customers. The food was fine overall. Someone, not sure if it's the cook or waiter forgot 3 different orders, 2 of which was for one person, while everyone else had plates in front of them. It was busy so we gave them some time (benefit of the doubt, we've worked in restaurants before) I'm about halfway in for my plate amount of time, so we notified the waiter about the misstep, doesn't know what's missing and asks us, don't think they even felt remotely sorry. Everyone else is finished by this point, it finally comes out and no real apologies, says sorry for the delay?? We're literally done with our food, this is no delay. I think an actual apology for forgetting 3 different orders is reasonable. Water was never re-filled either.
Always a great place to eat. Staff is friendly and food is well priced.
So tasty! Great service.

Really good sushi , affordable prices and great service. We chose to get king salmon seared with fire and this reminded us of the sushi we used to eat in Kyoto. It was melt in the mouth and incredibly delicious !
Their sushi is so fresh and super delicious. If there is a 6 star rating, I would definitely give them. Can't wait to come back again.
always enjoying
Fresh Japanese fish, beautifully arranged and it's the best sushi restaurant in Park Slope.

Had the pleasure of being served by the owner of the restaurant. The place was packed and he was incredibly speedy but was still able to serve top notch sushi with a sprinkle of very personable conversation.
Such a great place if you like high quality sushi. Also they serve good sake but it’s a bit pricey.
Very fresh fish, chef Leo is fun to talk with and have high standard for the food.
Excellent service, the fish was delish and tasted really fresh, cosy atmosphere, cost effective - the perfect place to grab lunch with a partner or  a couple of friends

I’ve eaten at this restaurant and had delicious sushi. Today I ordered delivery and the fish tasted very fishy and not fresh. I called the restaurant to inform them of this and the sushi chef called me back and reprimanded me and told me his fish is fresh. I’ve eaten sushi once a week for most of my life. I know when sushi isn’t fresh. I don’t need to be told what good sushi is. Very unprofessional and very disappointed.
Wow! Very small, low key, excellent sushi.
This place is pretty delicious and the service was really good. Had a wonderful time here.

Top quality sushi/sashimi - omakase - we were in Japan  for vacation this summer and won’t go anywhere else for sushi! Fresh and delicious. Excellent and friendly service. PS Better than or rivals Katsuei for authentic experience
Fresh & delicious sushi! Clean place with very nice service. Highly recommend, been here only for lunch but should try more often!
Food was good but very pricey. Sushi orders are only one piece for ~$5.

This is our new go-to NYC sushi spot. Very clean restaurant and very friendly staff. Sushi and beer was very delicious. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a good, quiet and relaxing place to have sushi. Will definitely be back.
Delicious
Amazing food.    Treat for your taste buds
Well done fresh and tasty sushy the desert amazing.
My go to sushi spot in the neighborhood. They are so nice and accommodating. Sushi is fresh and rolls are creative. The ramen is also fantastic!!

What a neighborhood gem that we stumbled upon!  Daily fish specials from Japan were clean and delicious.  Explored many different varieties of white fish and mackerel pike. Blown away by the Haikkido Uni (ordered twice, so nice).  Even the basics like medium fatty toro and salmon sashimi incredibly delicate. Have learned that the best sushi/sashimi is about the quality of ingredients AND how the chef's knife skills for texture and flavor.  Hard to find a place that does better at these prices. Go for adventure.  Kid friendly, too.
Amazing sushi at a reasonable price

The food is good But it’s not hard to find good sushi around this neighborhood  The portions are EXTREMELY small and the prices are EXTREMELY high.  Go anywhere else. These guys are greedy and they don’t deserve your business.  If you don’t mind a walk go to KI on smith or to Geido in Flatbush!
I order the chicken teriyaki here often. It's a little pricey but taste great! The restaurant has good customer service and a relaxing environment.
Excellent  appetizers, good selection of saki,  and fresh sashimi/sushi.
Pretty pricey, but you get what you pay for. Easily the best sushi I have ever had.
High quality sushi. If you are in the mood for Sushi, it's a great spot.
Had an amazing experience with Chef Joe! Quality was great and the prices were really fair! Definitely will visit again when I go back to Brooklyn
Nice little spot on 5th Avenue. A couple of tables and a bar.
Tasty ramen soup because it not too salty for me. Fresh shashimi and roll.
(Translated by Google) I did not like it very much, for the quality I feel it is a bit expensive.  (Original) No me gustó mucho, para la calidad siento que está un poco caro.

I would strongly recommend this restaurant, I came to Yashin with my family, the environment is clean and relaxing. The portion of every dish is also great. My favorite dish is omakase, it was recommended by a friend, and it was not a disappoint at all!
Fresh food and so yummy. People are very kind and dedicated to attend us.

This restaurant has a nice cozy atmosphere, we had an enjoyable dining experience here. The sashimi is so fresh, I really recommend fatty tuna, it’s so delicious. The staffs are also very welcoming and friendly when we stepped into the store. The price is reasonable.

I'm surprised with the rate this place has here on google and on yelp! Not clean AT ALL! Very average sushi and not fresh edamame! There are much better sushi places in Brooklyn! Don't recommend this one to anyone!

It is already my third time in this sushi restaurant because I really enjoy eating here. The raw fish is amazingly fresh and in a high hygiene condition. It also has many kinds of fishes I have never tried before. The sushi chef is very kind and friendly to talk. In addition, price is not crazily high or unaffordable.
Unlike other sushi place where they sell “fake sushi” this place actually has some quality in it, like the atmosphere,love the food, I would come back for some more fresh sushi.

Joe and Leo have created a very homey restaurant where you are welcomed like family.  Their sushi/sashimi is always delicious. The menu offers far more but we always stick with the sushi as we love it so. This is our go-to once a week Japanese restaurant. It's that good.

I love it here. The atmosphere is very inviting and relaxed.  It's nice to enjoy a spacious place on a block where many places are small.The quality of the sushi is very tasty.  When you're craving sushi this really hits the spot.
Excellent quality and OUTSTANDING service. This is a kid friendly place that takes pride in taking care of it's customers even the little one. I highly recommend Sushi Yasmin.
pretty solid.  Did find one bone
Tiny cosy and clean place. Tasty sashimi and algae, good products and jazz music on the background. Good!

Sweet little hidden gem run by a couple who take the utmost care in maintaining a high quality product. Their omakase is affordable but still memorable. Try that and the grilled fish collar (rotated daily).
Great sushi spot in Park Slope

The best part was that there was no one there, but then a mom and her kid came in and though every table in the restaurant was available, the waitress tried to seat them directly next to me. This seemed strange. It is a small place, and there were many tables within one or two steps where we wouldn't have to listen to each other masticating.  The mom and I looked at each other and her son wanted to sit by the window so he could look at his bike.  Crisis averted. There is hope in the youth.  Really good miso soup, sushi was pretty weak.  Had a dark cloud over my head throughout meal i had to go to the clinic for a clap test immediately after.  Good news though I'm clean.  Do not go to war without your Kevlar.
Very small space but sushi was fresh and delicious.
Would not recommend delivery.
Excellent food, quality of sushi is superb. Joe is the best!!

Best sushi in Brooklyn! They really live up to their mission of high quality fish at affordable prices! They also do omakase (not on the menu), but I highly recommend it. I have yet to eat anything here that I didn't like! Come check it out!!

This is a great restaurant. It's the best moderately priced sushi place in park slope and the owners are incredibly friendly. Make sure you check out the printed specials page. It lists the fresh stuff from Japan and all over.

i had dinner with my friend on weekend. We had ordered sashimi for 2. The fish so fresh and they had special menu also.we have tried the Japanese pepper n shrimp shumai.all the food that we ordered so good. I will come back again.

I came here because my friends high recommend,and I didn't disappointed,they just open 10 months,but they have so many regular customs,amazing fresh fish,which is they order everyday,and very friendly staff,nice service,and very good price,the sitting place is nice,located Conner place,nice sushi restaurant fell like went to Japan,and chef they know what they want do,best sushi restaurant in park slope,and they already got liquor license,I highly recommend,we will definitely come back.

Sorry to sound a bit racist, but when you spot your Japanese neighbor eating at a Japanese restaurant, you're going to want to try it right?  Right!  And I'm glad I did.  This restaurant replaced Corner Burger (which is still on Google Maps in case anyone is wondering) and it's a welcome addition to the plethora of Sushi restaurants in the neighborhood.  Fresh and reasonably priced, this dainty spot offers traditional fair and a ~$40-50 omakase (which I'll try next time).  Service is attentive and I love the wall outlets that allow patrons to charge their devices.

There's like three sushi joints within like a stone's throw away- but this is my favorite.  They're just really nice people who make good food. really cool decor too.  it's like homely (if that's a word).
Great, fresh food.  Sat at bar for lunch and chef was great to talk with.  We learned he modifies the soy sauce to an old Japanese recipe.
